comments.body:
Response from OIT:

***
This problem is typically caused by applications that redirect back to themselves multiple times, adding more cookie data or GET URLs each time. We've already increased the maximum headers size allowed by the SSO systems as much as we dare, but the problem still happens occasionally. Clearing browser caches or using new/private/incognito browser instances may temporarily work around the problem, but we cannot prevent all applications from misbehaving. At best, we can ask vendors to fix their applications.
Discussed at 12/15. Closing this OL ticket in favor of more general follow-up in https://github.com/pulibrary/dacs_handbook/issues/154.

pdc_describe.title: ignore empty rows in the creators

comments.body:
If one value is filled in for contributors then the blank row is also counted for contributors.  So contributors is utilizing the same code as creators, just it is not getting called until a value is stored.

![Screenshot 2023-12-15 at 3 20 12‚ÄØPM](https://github.com/pulibrary/pdc_describe/assets/1599081/a3370680-bad6-4b4b-8c56-bdf88d238c92)

Globus responded and asked for the output of `globus-connect-server self-diagnostic`

The output of the command is in [this document](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1_-V5vCfrk8VipDzfMitnLTFxuBczYo2Y/view?usp=drive_link) (which I am not posting the content here in case it has server details that we want to keep private)

A detail worth noting is this (NN.NN.NN.NN is our IP address)

```
== diagnostic: func:contact_info_uri() ==
Error accessing GCS Manager at NN.NN.NN.NN: HTTPSConnectionPool(host='NN.NN.NN.NN', port=443): 
Max retries exceeded with url: /api/info (Caused by ConnectTimeoutError(<urllib3.connection.HTTPSConnection 
object at 0x7f730c4704f0>, 'Connection to NN.NN.NN timed out. (connect timeout=1)'))
```

We are not sure what that means or how to address it, though.

Since we haven't heard from Globus support I rebooted the machine so that the Globus endpoint does not stay down over the weekend.

Globus endpoint is now alive and well: https://f0ad1.36fe.data.globus.org/api/info

Running `globus-connect-server self-diagnostic` does not report the error either.

Globus support responded and reported a few interesting things that they noted in our running environment. I've posted the response here: https://docs.google.com/document/d/1aCaUkRDhg7FTurElLeLTYmPPjA1jfXlvd_O16ZZIJHA/edit

Just for kicks I ran the self-diagnostic a couple of hours after the reboot logged the results in this file: https://drive.google.com/file/d/17L9ScYp0xC2-ahDp6yElsFkib4QXiUzi/view?usp=drive_link

Some of the numbers look already high to me (e.g. `Tasks: 680 (limit: 9384)`) but I wish I had checked immediately after the reboot. That number was `Tasks: 2101 (limit: 9384)` when we had the issue, though.

None of the processes look to be in "'uninterruptible sleep' state ('D' state in 'ps' output)" which is something they asked us to check.
